      • create

        public InternalKeyBinding create​(String type,
                                 int id,
                                 String name,
                                 InternalKeyBindingStatus status,
                                 String certificateId,
                                 int cryptoTokenId,
                                 String keyPairAlias,
                                 LinkedHashMap<Object,​Object> dataMap)
        Creates a new InternalKeyBinding instance.
        Parameters:
        type - is the alias of the registered InternalKeyBinding's type
        id - is the unique identifier of this InternalKeyBinding
        name - is the unique name that this InternalKeyBinding will be given
        status - the initial status to give the InternalKeyBinding
        certificateId - is the certificate fingerprint (lower case) matching the mapped key pair or null
        cryptoTokenId - is the CryptoToken id of the container where the mapped key pair is stored
        keyPairAlias - is the alias of the mapped key pair in the specified CryptoToken (may not be null)
        dataMap - is a Map of implementation specific properties for this type of IntenalKeyBinding
        Returns:
        a new InternalKeyBinding instance

      • validateProperties

        public InternalKeyBindingPropertyValidationWrapper validateProperties​(String alias,
                                                                      Map<String,​String> propertiesMap)
        Method to be used from an external environment (such as the CLI) where contextual information about a key binding implementation is not available. Will presume that all key binding properties were entered as strings, will return a data wrapper that contains a map of properly casted values, and information about any values which were either unknown or of an incorrect format.
        Parameters:
        alias - the alias of the key binding type to check for
        propertiesMap - the inputed properties, as strings
        Returns:
        a wrapper class that contains the correctly casted values, and information about any values that were invalid.
